# Server layer doctrine

`@mia/server` is the composition root (shell). Do **not** mirror agent’s
`domain/core/runtime` everywhere.

| Kind of code | Put it in |
| --- | --- |
| Process startup / shutdown | `boot/` |
| Fastify app composition | `http/` |
| SQLite, SSE, queue, sandbox, effects, MSSQL pools | `infra/` |
| Implementations of `@mia/agent` / `@mia/sync` ports | `adapters/` |
| HTTP product surface | `api/<surface>/` |
| Server-owned contracts | `ports/` |
| Server-only helpers / enum façades | `internal/` |
| CLI entrypoints | `cli/` |

**Retired names (do not recreate):** `bootstrap/`, `app/`, `features/`,
`platform/` (top-level), `shared/`, `api/runs/core/`, `hosting/`, `api/deploy/`.

## Naming that must stay unambiguous

- **Operator control plane:** `api/platform/` — never `api/deploy/`
- **Run prompt / tool-gating pure logic:** `api/runs/prompting/`
- Thin surfaces may be a single `routes.ts`

## Dependency direction

`api` → `infra` / `adapters` / `ports` / `internal`  
`infra` ↛ `api`  
`adapters` → `infra` / `ports` / `internal`  
`ports` → `ports` / `internal` (not api / infra impl)

Full contract: `docs/doctrine.md`. Enforce with `npm run lint:arch`.
